{"questionId":"11863","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = \\frac{{2x + 6}}{{{x^2} + 6x + 10}}{\\text{,}}\\,\\,x \\in \\mathbb{R}.\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>6</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>6</mn>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>10</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>.</mo>\n</math></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> has no vertical asymptotes.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{x^2} + 6x + 10 = {x^2} + 6x + 9 + 1 = {\\left( {x + 3} \\right)^2} + 1\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>10</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>9</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>So the denominator is never zero and thus there are no vertical asymptotes. (or use of discriminant is negative)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11863","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.4a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that f ( x ) has no vertical asymptotes.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.13—Rational functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}